# Message Template Domain

Authoritative contract: `docs/platforms/backend/contracts/message-template-domain.md`.

## Separation

- `MessageTemplate` stores **message library content** (and optional channel link), not SMTP/Ad Whats credentials.
- Credentials live on `MessageChannel` only (or the platform mailer for `EJTMAA_EMAIL`).

## Naming

- Template kind enum: `messageTemplateType` — `EJTMAA_EMAIL` | `CUSTOM_EMAIL` | `ADWHATS` | `ADWHATS_PRO`.
- Discriminator field on the model is `type` (not legacy `channel`).
- **Forbidden:** `messageTemplateChannel`, `WHATSAPP`, `EMAIL` as template kinds; do not confuse with `_MessageChannelType`.
- Do not invent a channel type `EJTMAA_EMAIL` — platform mail uses **no** channel row.

## Channel FK

- `message_channel_id` null **only** for `EJTMAA_EMAIL`.
- Other kinds require an org-owned channel whose `type` matches the template kind (`CUSTOM_EMAIL` / `ADWHATS` / `ADWHATS_PRO`).
- Write-path Joi/requester enforces this (not ORM nullability).
- ORM: `MessageTemplate.belongsTo(MessageChannel)` only. Do **not** add `MessageChannel.hasMany(MessageTemplate)` unless product/GQL also needs `_MessageChannel.messageTemplates` (circular import risk).
- Requester: `@requester("messageTemplate")` — website map `customer.messageTemplate`. Ability `MESSAGE_TEMPLATE` on `Customer`.
- Content by kind enforced in Joi with unused `.strip()`; persist flat `?? null` — **no** `attrsForType` (see `requester-type-conditional-strip.mdc`).
- `ADWHATS_PRO` requires `meta_template_id` + `variables` JSONB map.
- `read` must **not** echo `messageTemplate` id. Update locks `type`.
- `read` hydrate for choice/picker fields follows `requester-read-select-hydrate.md` (`toEnumForSelect` + `MessageChannel.forSelect`).
- `delete` blocked when a Meeting still references the template (`whatsapp_template_id` / `email_template_id`) via `CANNOT_DELETE_USED`.

## Content by kind

| type | subject/body | meta_template_id | variables |
|---|---|---|---|
| `EJTMAA_EMAIL` / `CUSTOM_EMAIL` | required on write | null | null |
| `ADWHATS` | body only | null | null |
| `ADWHATS_PRO` | null | required on write | JSONB `Record<string, string>` |

## GQL

- `_MessageTemplate` exposes `type`, `messageChannel`, `subject`, `body`, `variables` (`JSONObject`), `meta_template_id`.
- `_MessageChannelFilter` supports `type` + `status` (picker: `ACTIVE` + matching type).
- `MessageChannelBridge.GetOneParent` must include `MessageTemplateModel` for nested `messageChannel`.
- Meeting FKs stay `whatsapp_template_id` / `email_template_id` until an explicit rename slice.

## After SDL changes

Backend `yarn generate-types`, then mirror `base`/`customer` SDL + gql-types into `website/`.
